title: New Data Reveals Exactly How Much Super You Need For Retirement | 10 News+
description: The high cost of electricity is being cited as having an impact on how much money people need in their super before they retire. title: Ten Dead In Peru Karaoke Bar Fire Triggered by Gas Blast | 10 News
description: A gas cylinder explosion sparked a fire at a restaurant and karaoke bar in Huancane, Peru, killing 10 people, including eight students, and leaving three others seriously injured.  The blaze tore through the building on Thursday, with neighbours trying to contain the flames as the town’s lack of a fire brigade delayed help.  Authorities said the venue had no working extinguishers or visible emergency exits.  The tragedy has renewed scrutiny of safety enforcement in entertainment venues across the Puno region. title: Donald Trump Awarded Controversial FIFA Peace Prize At World Cup 2026 Draw | 10 News
description: FIFA President Gianni Infantino sparked controversy by awarding Donald Trump the first-ever FIFA peace prize - with no listed nominees or finalists and no vote by FIFA’s Council - ahead of the 2026 World Cup draw.  The award was presented on stage at Washington’s Kennedy Centre by FIFA President Gianni Infantino.  Trump called it “one of the great honours” and claimed “we saved millions of lives.”  Trump has made disputed claims about conflicts he has “ended,” despite launching controversial military actions and facing criticism that his self-proclaimed peace efforts in Gaza and Ukraine were one-sided and ineffective.  Infantino praised Trump’s role in the Abrahams Accord, the Gaza peace deal and the Rwanda-DRC agreement.  The move has drawn scrutiny given FIFA’s own rules requiring political neutrality in dealings with governments.
